Russian Equity Movers: Gazprom Neft, Norilsk Shares Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-04T15:46:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/russian-equity-movers-lukoil-transneft-uralkali-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  sank 2.1
percent to 1,620.68 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, erasing an
earlier gain of as much as 0.9 percent. The dollar-denominated
RTS Index declined 2.4 percent to 1,855.69.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX), the oil arm of  Russia ’s natural
gas export monopoly, dropped for a third day, sliding 3.1
percent to 126.42 rubles. Crude oil fell $1.72 to $90.32 a
barrel at the close of equities trading in Moscow from the same
time yesterday.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX), Russia’s biggest mining
company, decreased to its lowest in five weeks, retreating 1.5
percent to 7,140 rubles. Nickel, copper and tin slid on the
London Metal Exchange amid signs the global recovery is
stalling, damping demand for commodities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
